-- UGB to Sell Tunis Bank Stake to Burgan as Part of $725 Million Asset Sale
-- Arif Sharif
-- 2010-06-13T11:44:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-13/ugb-to-sell-tunis-bank-stake-to-burgan-as-part-of-725-million-asset-sale.html

          
          
             United Gulf Bank BSC, a Bahrain-
based investment bank, plans to sell a stake in Tunis
International Bank to Burgan Bank SAK of Kuwait as part of a
plan to dispose its stakes in four banks for $725 million.  
 The sale of its holding in Algeria Gulf Bank, Bank of
Baghdad and Jordan Kuwait Bank has been completed and the
disposal of its stake in Tunis International will be completed
once regulatory approval has been received, United Gulf Bank
said in a statement to the Bahrain Stock Exchange today.  
